
@startuml

' Classes
class Customer {
  -id: int
  -name: String
  -address: String
  -status: String (Active, Suspended)
  -fuelCard: FuelCard
}

class FuelCard {
  -cardNumber: String
  -customer: Customer
  -transactions: List<Transaction>
}

class Transaction {
  -id: int
  -date: Date
  -amount: double
  -pump: Pump
  -invoice: Invoice
}

class Invoice {
  -id: int
  -month: Date
  -customer: Customer
  -totalAmount: double
  -discount: double
  -paid: boolean
  -transactions: List<Transaction>
}

class Payment {
  -id: int
  -date: Date
  -amount: double
  -invoice: Invoice
}

class GasStation {
  -id: int
  -name: String
  -location: String
  -pumps: List<Pump>
}

class Pump {
  -id: int
  -type: String (e.g., Regular, Diesel)
  -gasLevel: double
  -reorderLevel: double
  -criticalLevel: double
  -reservoir: Reservoir
  -status: String (Available, Blocked, Refilling)
  -refillRequests: List<RefillRequest>
  -transactions: List<Transaction>
}

class Reservoir {
  -id: int
  -capacity: double
  -currentLevel: double
}

class RefillRequest {
  -id: int
  -pump: Pump
  -requestDate: Date
  -quantityToOrder: double
}

class DailyReport {
  -id: int
  -reportDate: Date
  -refillRequests: List<RefillRequest>
}

' Relationships
Customer "1" -- "1" FuelCard : owns
FuelCard "1" -- "*" Transaction : has
Transaction "1" -- "0..1" Invoice : belongs to
Invoice "1" -- "*" Payment : can have multiple
GasStation "1" -- "*" Pump : contains
Pump "1" -- "1" Reservoir : has
Pump "1" -- "*" RefillRequest : generates
Pump "1" -- "*" Transaction : processes
DailyReport "1" -- "*" RefillRequest : includes

' Inheritance or association notes
note right of Invoice
  An invoice is sent once per month.
  Discounts are applied based on customer's turnover.
  A customer can receive multiple invoices before paying.
end note

note right of Pump
  When gas level drops below reorderLevel, a refill request is generated.
  If gas level drops below criticalLevel, pump is blocked.
  After refill, pump is temporarily blocked for ~1 hour.
end note

note right of Customer
  Customers can be suspended if they fail to pay two consecutive invoices.
  Slack is given based on customer history.
end note

@enduml

---

### 📌 Summary of Key Entities:

- **Customer**: Owns a fuel card and may be active or suspended.
- **FuelCard**: Used to make refuel transactions without immediate payment.
- **Transaction**: Represents a single refueling event at a pump.
- **Invoice**: Monthly billing for all refuel transactions made with a fuel card.
- **Payment**: Records when an invoice is paid.
- **GasStation**: Manages pumps and generates reports.
- **Pump**: Handles refueling and tracks gasoline levels.
- **Reservoir**: Contains fuel for a specific pump.
- **RefillRequest**: Generated when fuel needs to be replenished.
- **DailyReport**: Aggregates all refill requests for daily monitoring.

